trine and Covenants 110:1–16</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:5>3.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:5><p data-aid=143140112 id=note3_p1>Karl Ricks Anderson, <cite>The Savior in Kirtland: Personal Accounts of Divine Manifestations</cite> (2012), 276; <a class="" href=/#note3>Doctrine and Covenants 38:33</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:7>4.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:7><p data-aid=143140114 id=note4_p1>Given in the apostolic charge administered by Oliver Cowdery, in “<a class="" href=/#note4>Minute Book 1</a>,” Feb. 21, 1835, 162, josephsmithpapers.org.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:9>5.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:9><p data-aid=143140115 id=note5_p1>Joseph Fielding Smith, <cite>Doctrines of Salvation,</cite> comp. Bruce R. McConkie (1955), 2:234.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:11>6.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:11><p data-aid=143140118 id=note6_p1><a class="" href=/#note6>Doctrine and Covenants 38:32</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:13>7.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:13><p data-aid=143140119 id=note7_p1>See James B. Allen, Ronald K. Esplin, and David J. Whittaker, <cite>Men with a Mission: The Quorum of the Twelve Apostles in the British Isles, 1837–1841</cite> (1992), 53, 302; Brandon S. Plewe, ed., <cite>Mapping Mormonism: An Atlas of Latter-day Saint History</cite> (2012), 104.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:15>8.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:15><p data-aid=143140120 id=note8_p1><a class="" href=/#note8>Doctrine and Covenants 110:14–16</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:17>9.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:17><p data-aid=143140121 id=note9_p1><a class="" href=/#note9>2 Nephi 28:30</a>.</p></div></section></div></div></aside></div></main><div><div><script type=text/javascript> var channel = 'www.lds.org'; var pageName = 'www.lds.org:""'; var locale = '"eng"'; var LDS = LDS || { }; LDS.track = LDS.track || { }; LDS.track.pageName = pageName; LDS.track.channel = channel; LDS.track.prop35 = locale; if (typeof(searchType) !== 'undef